<TEXT>
quiet on the set is an offbroadway play 
thats fun several layers of soap opera froth though its 
slightly more fun in the idea than the delivery 
the play is about the actors on a tv daytime drama and their 
offscreen lives which are as tangled as the plot of their show 
the play opened wednesday at the orpheum theater 
its a chance for two couples to overact on purpose put on the 
throaty overdramatic voice of the soaps and breathe lines like 
thats a long and sordid story 
the five actors and the writer of quiet on the set are soap 
opera stars trent bushey plays david rampal kate collins plays 
natalie hunter cady mcclain plays dixie cooney and matt servitto 
plays trask bodine on all my children robert newman plays 
joshua lewis and playwright terrell anthony played rusty shayne on 
guiding light 
the plot of the soapwithintheplay sunset involves a 
young woman who returns home to her sister after miscarrying the 
child of a rich married man and running away from another man to 
whom she had turned the second man tracks her down and turns out 
to be the first mans brother 
in real life busheys character is a beginner an insecure 
goofup who maddeningly wants to analyze scenes newman is newly 
sober trying to make a comeback getting his role on sunset 
through his sister mcclain he was previously the star of another 
soap fired his lover collins then lost his job through cocaine 
and alcohol collins carries bitchy vindictiveness beyond the 
sunset set 
servitto is in and out as comic relief in a series of campy 
cliche parts a deliveryman a hairdresser a stagehand who snores 
through a love scene 
director ac weary got his start directing on another world 
and guiding light coup de grace productions in association 
with 126 second ave corp produced the show which was first seen 
at the westbeth theater center 
quiet on the set is fun but has its slow spots kind of like 
a soap opera 
</TEXT>
