in a petition filed with the national labor 
relations board a technical union at nbc accused the company of 
unfair labor practices nbc immediately denied the accusations 
the charges by the national association of broadcast employees 
and technicians were filed on the same day nbc put in effect 
fouryear contract proposal that a majority of the unions members 
at nbc have rejected twice 
the union which represents 2373 employees at nbc and nbcowned 
facilities accused the company of failing and refusing to 
bargain in good faith its previous contract expired on march 31 
nbc has fully met its obligations under the national labor 
relations act said nbc spokesman joe rutledge who said the 
companys final offer came after more than seven months of 
negotiations and 35 separate meetings 
were confident that just as when nabet filed a similar 
complaint in 1987 the nlrb will find the charges without merit 
the 1987 charge was filed during a bitter strike by the union 
that lasted 17 weeks no walkout this time is imminent no strike 
vote has been taken and union officials say theyll probably go to 
court to fight nbcs action 
