bandits armed with an uzi robbed a pair of 
fbi agents wednesday and fled in a government car full of weapons 
and radio equipment stolen from one of the lawmen police said 
no one was injured in the robbery that occurred at 1230 pm 
when the two agents in separate government vehicles stopped on a 
street to discuss a case said police sgt greg correa 
as they were talking a car drove up and the passenger jumped 
out carrying an uzi said correa he pointed it at one of the 
agents who jumped out of his car ran away and leaped over a fence 
to safety 
the gunman ordered the other agent out of his car then got in 
the government vehicle and sped away the sergeant said the 
gunmans accomplice followed in the car the pair had arrived in 
the stolen government car contained three handguns a shotgun 
expensive radio equipment the agents badge and information on 
active fbi cases correa said 
the agents names and the robbery location were withheld 
fred reagan spokesman for the fbi office in los angeles could 
not be immediately reached for comment 
