rescuers today found a solo 
climber who survived six days in a mountain blizzard that killed 
six soldiers 
jo ji iwama a 27yearold native of japan who manages a steak 
restaurant in auckland was airlifted off 9230foot mount ruapehu 
he said he had no injuries and looked forward to a steak hot soup 
and a beer 
he said he survived by digging a cave in the snow and eating a 
cookie for breakfast chocolate for lunch and candy for dinner he 
kept warm by doing pushups 
there was a whiteout and terrible freezing conditions 20 or 
35 minutes after i left the snow cave he said he was found as 
he tried to make his way back down the mountain 
the bodies of the servicemen who were taking part in army 
training were also lifted off the mountain today 
