magellans formal program to make detailed maps and pictures of 
venus starts aug 29 or sept 1 the national aeronautics and space 
administration plans to release the first images during september 
venus the second planet from the sun is covered by thick 
clouds so radar must be used to make images of its surface 
the radar was turned on for an hour wednesday just to show it 
was working for the first time since magellan went into orbit 
around venus last friday after a 948millionmile trip from earth 
the radar previously was turned on for tests during may and 
