<TEXT>
aids has become the leading cause of death 
among adult men in the west african city of abidjan the magazine 
science says it is the second most common cause in adult women 
there after deaths related to pregnancy and abortion 
a recent study in the ivory coast capital city found a minimum 
annual incidence of aids of 1447 cases per million in adult men 
and 340 per million in adult women science said in its aug 17 
edition 
the study of cadavers was done in a 62day and 43day period 
among 698 adult bodies examined 41 percent of men and 32 percent 
of women were infected with hiv the agent that causes acquired 
immune deficiency syndrome the highest rates were found in men and 
women aged 30 to 39 
science said the figures probably underestimate the true 
mortality due to hiv infection among factors skewing the figures 
were the exclusion of pediatric patients the unknown proportion of 
aids deaths not brought to the mortuaries studied and the cultural 
practice of seriously ill persons leaving abidjan to die in their 
home areas 
in addition deaths due to pulmonary tuberculosis the third 
ranking cause of male adult death specifically were not counted 
as aids cases although 50 percent of such cadavers tested hiv 
positive 
although data concerning mortality due to aids are scarce 
the article said aids is likely to be the leading cause of adult 
death in a number of other african cities also 
in the united states according to the centers for disease 
control there were 161 cases of aids per 100000 population in 
the year ending in july 
