the austerity program recommended by the international monetary 
fund which lends to developing countries was aimed at cutting an 
inflation rate of more than 50 percent 
the government cut subsidies on a series of basic consumer 
items including gasoline sugar and flour gasoline went up 836 
percent from 55 cents a gallon to 107 
the minimum monthly salaries are 69 for public employees and 
96 for private sector employees 
the country whose largest export item is sugar was hit hard by 
a fall in sugar prices and its unemployment rate is about 25 
percent electricity blackouts and currency devaluations are common 
