<TEXT>
russian leader boris n yeltsin said thursday he 
and soviet president mikhail s gorbachev are interrupting their 
summer trips and returning to moscow to salvage their emergency 
plan for rescuing the soviet economy 
yeltsin president of the vast russian republic on wednesday 
broke off his threeweek tour of the republic to join in drafting 
the economic program according to the official tass news agency 
yeltsin also told tass that gorbachev was returning to moscow 
from the southern crimea where he had been expected to vacation 
for a month 
yeltsin said tuesday a conflict had developed within the 
12member commission that he and gorbachev appointed earlier this 
month to develop a joint blueprint for moving toward a market 
economy the russian president did not specify what issue was in 
dispute 
after meeting with commission members thursday yeltsin said the 
members were having trouble getting information from the soviet 
finance and defense ministries which control vital sectors of the 
economy but he said without elaborating that they agreed on 
measures to avoid chaos during the changeover from a command 
economy to a marketoriented system that both men envision 
yeltsin also accused soviet prime minister nikolai ryzhkov of 
duplicating the commissions work by developing a parallel economic 
plan 
it is necessary to concentrate on our program which is 
trusted by the people and is both novel and realistic tass 
quoted yeltsin as saying 
yeltsin said if both plans are presented to the national 
parliament for approval in september russia will adopt its own 
plan and the issue will be closed 
gorbachev has ordered all national government agencies to 
cooperate with the highlevel economy commission 
however yeltsin complained that the commission has not even 
obtained a breakdown of the current soviet budget and blamed 
bureaucratic obstacles on either a lack of desire or sabotage 
according to the interfax news agency of radio moscow 
members of the commission include gorbachevs top economic 
adviser nikolai y petrakov a strong proponent of market reforms 
deputy prime minister leonid a abalkin presidential council 
member stanislav shatalin and officials of the russian republic 
yeltsin said the economic package could be implemented by oct 
1 he said its top priority would be to stabilize the economy to 
improve the circulation of money it would strengthen the ruble by 
jan 1 
the economy is unable to provide enough housing food or basic 
consumer goods for the soviet people and economists blame part of 
the problem on an excess supply of rubles and inefficient 
production and distribution 
yeltsin said gorbachev has been in daily telephone contact with 
the commission since beginning his vacation in early august 
as far as i know gorbachev decided to cut short his 
vacation in order to come here and personally supervise the work 
yeltsin told reporters 
it was not known when gorbachev would return to the capital 
yeltsin on aug 6 began a tour of russia which encompasses 
threequarters of the soviet land mass and half its population he 
is scheduled to go back on the road to novokuznetsk on friday 
during his meetings in local communities yeltsin has suggested 
russia will borrow 7 billion to 10 billion from the west to ease 
food shortages and promised that all businesses in the republic 
will be free to run their own affairs beginning jan 1 
he said russia will study national construction and development 
programs including space and stop financing those which are 
unprofitable he also pledged to contribute only 36 billion to the 
national budget compared with 112 billion in past years he also 
said he will press for a 15 percent cut in national defense 
spending 
russia already has claimed sovereignty over its natural 
resources and last week yeltsin declared invalid all contracts 
signed by the central government to sell those resources that 
includes a 5 billion deal to sell russias diamonds to the de 
beers diamond syndicate 
on wednesday he said russia would set a maximum income tax of 
38 percent and that it would be lower for entrepreneurs who 
stimulated the economy by creating jobs 
yeltsin was elected president in june and quit the communist 
party in july saying he wanted to devote more time to his new 
duties 
