have to live with that sort of thing eaton said at a press 
briefing i dont feel offended i dont feel disgusted i dont 
feel amused its a point of view i dont happen to share 
ulysses scientific instruments would be powered by one 
radioisotope thermoelectric generator or rtg which converts heat 
from decaying plutonium into electricity the generators have been 
used without mishap on 23 space missions many of them planetary 
probes during the past few decades said willis meeks ulysses 
project manager for nasa 
it would be the second time an rtg has flown on the shuttle 
last october two such generators were aboard the galileo 
spacecraft that was sent by the shuttle atlantis on a sixyear 
journey to jupiter 
opponents want the ulysses mission postponed until solar panels 
can be installed as a power source 
however such a redesign would likely kill the program said 
edward smith ulysses project scientist the united states does not 
