the marine corps is building to a force of 
45000 in the mideast in its largest deployment since the vietnam 
war pentagon sources said thursday 
the forces include ground troops and amphibious units from 
around the globe said the sources who spoke only on condition of 
anonymity 
separately gen john dailey the assistant commandant of the 
marine corps said the service is sending a substantial armada 
of assault troops by air and sea to saudi arabia though he 
declined to estimate a number 
he said the marines would provide significant combat 
capability in defense of saudi arabia and would be ready for a 
prolonged stay 
we dont just arrive the fourstar general said in an 
interview were there to stay for a fairly lengthy period 
