kennebunkport maine said some consideration was being given 
to calling up military reserve units to back up troops being sent 
to the middle east 
he said the reserves were ready to serve but no decision has 
been made in that regard 
the marine buildup is just one part of what has become an 
enormous movement of sea air and ground forces to the mideast 
president bush and the nations military leaders have kept secret 
the exact number of us troops responding to the twoweek old 
persian gulf crisis but officials have prepared contingency plans 
to put 250000 soldiers on the ground if necessary 
