condition of anonymity said units are being pulled together from 
around the globe including bases on both us coasts hawaii and 
okinawa 
in the main components the sources said 
marine combat forces from bases at camp pendleton el toro and 
twentynine palms calif are being flown to saudi arabia 
elements of marine units from norfolk va as well as camp 
lejeune cherry point and new river in north carolina will become 
part of a 13ship amphibious assault task force that will be 
leaving within days 
a third brigade is on alert and preparing to join the other 
two for a total force that is expected to number around 45000 men 
if all units are deployed 
the third unit also composed of amphibious forces will remain 
floating off the coastal waters of saudi arabia ready to land 
and project power anywhere on the peninsula the sources said 
