sidewinder missiles and an array of troop transports attack 
helicopters and light armored vehicles armed with 25 mm canons 
all units arrive with the fuel ammunition and waterpurifying 
capabilities that will allow them to fight and sustain combat for 
30 days 
gen dailey in an interview thursday said the marine corps is 
particularly suited to dealing with the saudi crisis since its men 
can move with speed to an area with a formidable combat 
capability and yet remain off shore if necessary it gives us 
the opportunity to do nothing to use nonprovocative means if 
a crisis subsides dailey said 
the deployment to the middle east which has put marines on the 
ground in saudi arabia within six days of receiving their first 
alert shows the worth of prepositioning equipment and supplies 
at strategic points around the globe dailey said 
such supplies are stored at the us base at diego garcia in the 
indian ocean on guam and on the east coast of the united states 
the marine forces in saudi arabia will be under the command of 
