assertive said lt gen carl mundy commanding general of fleet 
marine force atlantic 
the barn doors are open and all the marine corps spigots are 
wide open mundy said adding that the movement would last until 
next week 
the number of marines being readied for deployment to the 
mideast amounts to a substantial segment of the 197000strong 
force even though a marine amphibious readiness group is helping 
conduct the evacuation operation off the west coast of africa due 
to the civil war in liberia dailey said the service isnt stressed 
and sees no need to call up reservists 
