<TEXT>
dr john walker a retired surgeon 
and investment banker and uncle of president bush died thursday of 
complications from an aneurism he was 81 
walker died in southern maine medical center in biddeford 
maine near this coastal resort where the walker family has 
summered since the turn of the century 
walker was stricken and rushed to the hospital wednesday night 
the president drove to the hospital thursday morning but arrived 
shortly after his uncles death 
walker lived in retirement on a farm on marylands eastern shore 
and spent winters in hobe sound fla 
a surgeon who was graduated from yale and the columbia medical 
school he switched careers from medicine to finance after he was 
stricken with polio in 1950 he became a managing partner in gh 
walker and co in new york and a limited partner of alex brown inc 
he also became president of sloan kettering memorial hospital in 
new york city according to the white house press office 
it was on walkers recommendation that the bushes brought their 
3yearold daughter robin to sloan kettering for treatment in 1953 
after a doctor in midland texas told them she was dying of 
leukemia 
bush in his 1987 autobiography looking forward wrote 
after we came home from the doctors office i called my 
uncle dr john walker in new york city he was president of 
memorial hospital there and a former cancer specialist when i told 
him the news about robin he urged us to bring her to new york 
where early research into leukemia was being conducted at memorial 
hospital by the sloankettering foundation maybe nothing could be 
done he told us but we would never forgive ourselves if we didnt 
try even if the odds were a hundred million to one said john 
youve got to give life a chance 
the little girl spent the last six months of her life at the 
cancer center where barbara bush stayed at her bedside while 
george bush shuttled between midland and new york city she died in 
november 1953 a few weeks short of her fourth birthday 
walker was an army major in world war ii serving in the 
european theater the son of the donor of the walker cup he was an 
avid golfer until stricken by polio 
he is survived by his wife louise mead walker three sons 
judge john m walker of new york city george mead walker of 
severna park md randolph talbott walker of easton md and a 
daughter elsie walker kilborne of narberth pa a second daughter 
lulie wear walker died in 1955 from polio 
also surviving are his two sisters dorothy walker bush and 
nancy walker two brothers louis and james and six grandchildren 
a private funeral service will be held tuesday at st anns 
episcopal church in kennebunkport 
