savage handtohand fighting 
between rival black factions spread thursday into soweto where men 
with spears and axes rampaged through a train station hacking 
terrified passengers to death 
police and the african national congress agreed to hold a 
peace forum friday to try to halt the violence between zulus 
and xhosas that left at least 156 people dead in five days 
hundreds of zulus fell upon railway passengers witnesses said 
pulling screaming people from the platform killing several and 
wounding many 
