<TEXT>
shakespeares richard iii is such a monster that 
it takes a truly dangerous actor to play him dangerous in the 
sense of not playing it safe 
an actor has to pull out all the stops even go a bit overboard 
to portray the evil genius who murders and connives his way to the 
throne after all this man has to convince a lot of people that he 
should be king 
but denzel washington holds back in the new production of 
richard iii which joseph papps new york shakespeare festival 
has on view in central park through sept 2 
washingtons tyrant is more mannered than monstrous he speaks 
in clipped phrases that rob the character of much of richards 
malicious persona the actor hesitates something that doesnt fit 
with the kings calculating histrionics the man should mesmerize 
be larger than life in this production he gets lost in the crowd 
even richards physical deformities have been lessened the 
hunchback is gone and the game leg more a limp than a major 
liability washington is an attractive easygoing performer which 
works against him in this role 
still the actor may grow in confidence as he continues to play 
the part and director robin phillips has surrounded washington 
with a generally fine cast and an intelligent straightforward 
production 
phillips presents nearly the entire play which is one of the 
longer works in the shakespeare canon he balances the pageantry 
and the intimate scenes well the best moments are the oneonone 
confrontations richards wooing of lady anne whose husband and 
fatherinlaw he has just murdered and his arguments with queen 
elizabeth after he has killed her two sons 
the other roles in the play are purely secondary but there are 
impressive cameos by mary alice as that onewoman chorus of doom 
queen margaret daniel davis as richards willing and eventually 
doomed coconspirator buckingham and sam tsoutsouvas as the 
dying king edward iv 
the setting by elis y lam is hightech allpurpose middle ages 
with towering arches and a movable backdrop of iron grating that 
conveniently serves as a prison when lowered into place 
lams costumes are sumptuous especially the dazzling dark blue 
cape bestowed on richard when he is finally crowned 
like all the history plays richard iii is about power 
specifically the misuse of power and how england overcame the 
rulers who misused power 
phillips comes up with a stunning tableau at the end of the 
play the dead richard lies downstage while the victorious henry 
earl of richmond who becomes henry vii is carried off in triumph 
by a cheering crowd 
its a fitting climax to shakespeares history plays that begin 
with richard ii and work their way through henry iv parts 
1 and 2 henry v and the three parts of henry vi now if 
only the richard of this production could match the monster that 
shakespeare put on stage 
</TEXT>
