<TEXT>
the pilot of a hotair balloon involved 
in an accident that killed 13 people was arrested thursday as he 
tried to leave the country 
the pilot michael sanby has not been charged in the accident 
last year near alice springs in central australia but alice 
springs coroner denis barrett heard a recommendation earlier this 
week that sanby face 13 counts of manslaughter 
northern territory police had issued a provisional warrant for 
his arrest 
police said sanby was arrested thursday as he attempted to board 
a qantas flight from perth to singapore 
frank gaffy a lawyer assisting the coroner in his 
investigation said there is evidence sanby deliberately collided 
with another balloon in the accident on aug 13 1989 
the coroners court has heard how the basket of sanbys balloon 
hit and tore open the envelope of a lower balloon carrying 13 
people gaffy has said the pilots intention was to touch the 
envelope of the crashed ballon to give passengers a thrill 
barrett is expected to make recommendations monday on any 
charges related to the accident 
