the adventures of ozzie and harriet 
one of the most watched shows in television history was the 
perfect vehicle for the budding music career of the sitcoms 
teenage star 
an awkward lipsynced performance of im walkin blasted 
ricky nelson to the top of the charts a few weeks after the episode 
aired with 60000 copies of the single sold in three days 
years later the same tv teenidol image would obscure ricks 
status as an important figure in pop music history the last link 
to genuine rock n roll and the progenitor of california rock 
the association with the television show was death to rick 
that more than anything is what did him in as far as his image 
went said san francisco rock critic joel selvin author of a 
biography of rick nelson whose 1985 death in an airplane crash 
shocked the nation 
there is no way you could survive coming out of ozzie and 
harriet and be seen as a real authentic rock and roller 
nelsons death is still linked in the publics mind to his 
cocaine use in ricky nelson idol for a nation contemporary 
books 1895 selvin attempts to set the record straight 
the plane crash initially was tied to alleged cocaine freebasing 
aboard the craft however a few weeks after the crash selvin 
writes the investigation focused almost exclusively on the 
troublesome heater in the rear of the passenger cabin the 
testimony was released to the press but headlines about the heater 
starting the fire didnt make quite the splash the freebasing rumor 
did two months before 
in the biography selvin emphasizes the significance of rickys 
california rockabilly a genre he began and how his 
charmed youth produced a nightmarish adulthood marred by heavy 
drug use and a roller coaster career 
the book starts with witness descriptions of the texas crash of 
a world war iivintage douglas dc3 that killed the singer his 
girlfriend and some band members it flashes back to ozzie and 
harriets early years together then traces their sons life and 
career winding up with his starstudded funeral 
detailed attention is given to rickys late 1950s recordings 
which selvin says rank easily with the best of buddy holly the 
everly brothers and elvis 
selvin takes the reader to the lew chuddproduced sessions for 
imperial records that created waitin in school stood up 
believe what you say and my buckets got a hole in it many 
featuring the stinging solos of guitar great james burton 
the book also looks at the darker side of the performers life 
a humdrum acting career a deeply troubled marriage to kristin 
harmon and finally his last days as an isolated drug addict so 
burned out that he wore makeup when he ventured from his mulholland 
drive home 
selvin a critic for the san francisco chronicle for the past 18 
years said hes been a nelson fan since the early 1970s when the 
singer won acclaim for his work with the countryrock stone canyon 
band the same era produced garden party the only outstanding 
song rick wrote 
that song connected with the most important emotional issue of 
his life the lack of acknowledgement for his authentic musical 
accomplishments selvin said 
research and writing the book took six months much of which the 
author spent interviewing friends and musicians who worked with 
rick 
aside from older brother david nelson who sat still for a 
few interviews the family was no help whatsoever selvin said 
harriet nelson and harmon refused to meet with the biographer 
its a funny thing about the nelson family wherever you go 
people have a little story david has the same story it starts 
with the phrase they were just like the tv show which is just 
not so ricky would have been the first to say that selvin said 
though much of the book will appeal to music history buffs 
selvin digs up enough dirt to draw in fans of tellall hollywood 
biographies he depicts the hardworking ozzie nelson as a 
domineering stifling influence on his sons 
whereas the nelsons of tvland were a nice normal middleclass 
family the real nelsons were millionaires hollywood elite on the 
show david was a lawyer in reality he flunked out of high 
school selvin said 
