despite what happened before and despite the virtual certainty 
that something similar would happen again us efforts at energy 
discipline were shelved for most of a decade ronald reagans 
energy policy was to leave it alone and let the market rule that 
sufficed while middle east oil was plentiful and relatively cheap 
now the problem is back 
we have spent the last decade basking in the glow of falling 
real energy prices sen albert gore jr dtenn said before 
