<TEXT>
american stores co has agreed to sell its 
buttrey food and drug division for 184 million to a group led by 
the managers of the chain 
the sale expected to be completed within 60 days will include 
180 million in cash and about 4 million in lease assumptions 
american stores said wednesday 
buttrey management teamed up with the los angelesbased merchant 
banking firm freeman spogli amp co to make the purchase the buyers 
are expected to continue to operate the division now headquartered 
in great falls mont under the buttrey name and with few changes 
the buttrey chain which employs about 4200 people at 44 stores 
in montana washington wyoming idaho and north dakota has annual 
sales of about 476 million 
american stores said in may that buttrey was among its marginal 
performing assets that were being assessed for possible sale 
american stores said though buttreys sales and earnigs were 
improving they were not performing at desired levels 
following the buttrey sale american stores will operate 1857 
food and drug stores in 37 states american stores based in salt 
lake city reported profits of 118 million on sales of 22 billion 
for the fiscal year ended feb 2 
</TEXT>
