stock prices dropped today after the government 
reported that inflation rose last month at a rate greater than 
economists expected 
the dow jones average of 30 industrial stocks fell 2005 points 
to 272822 in the first hour and a half of trading 
in the broader market declining issues outnumbered advancing 
ones by more than a 3 to 1 margin on the new york stock exchange 
with 291 up 932 down and 476 unchanged 
volume on the floor of the big board totaled 4255 million 
shares as of 11 am on wall street 
analysts said the july consumer price report was bad news for 
the markets the labor department said prices excluding the 
volatile food and energy sector rose 06 percent last month while 
overall prices rose 04 percent higher than the 03 percent most 
economists expected 
the department pointed out that the data was collected before 
the start of the mideast crisis which has sent oil prices surging 
the report also caused bond prices to fall sharply 
also today the commerce department said housing starts 
continued to plummet in july falling 26 percent to their lowest 
level since september 1982 
despite the weakness in housing economists said the bad news on 
inflation gave the federal reserve little room to stimulate the 
economy by lowering interest rates 
the us stock markets received little help from abroad today 
stock prices fell in japan with the key index on the tokyo 
exchange closing 2 percent lower prices also were down in london 
among mostactive bluechip issues today philip morris fell 
to 46 ibm was down lsqb to 104 general electric lost to 65 and 
american express fell to 26rsqb 
the nyse composite index of all its listed common shares fell 
128 to 18526 at the american stock exchange the market value 
index stood at 33921 down 143 
