<TEXT>
ames department stores inc said it will 
close its regional accounting office here as part a companywide 
plan to consolidate jobs and cut costs 
the closing of ames downtown syracuse office will put nearly 
160 people out of work company spokesman bill roberts said 
wednesday 
ames filed for chapter 11 protection under the us bankruptcy 
code in april just two years after acquiring the zayre discount 
store chain 
zayre had an accounting operation in syracuse ames decided to 
move some of its operations from its headquarters in rocky hill 
conn to syracuse those responsibilities will now be shifted back 
to rocky hill said roberts 
roberts said that probably fewer than 10 jobs would be 
transferred to rocky hill most of the jobs in the accounting 
office are clerical 
ames plans to close 221 stores nationwide as part of a 
consolidation 
</TEXT>
