the us dollar rose thursday in european trading 
dominated by anxiety over the gulf crisis 
gold ended the day moderately higher 
dealers said while there were no new trends in the market the 
dollar moved higher as world oil prices strengthened 
were waiting for the next inspiration said the chief 
dealer of a us regional bank in london that may be military 
rather than economic 
dealers were also watching the meeting between jordans king 
hussein and president bush for signs of any diplomatic breakthrough 
in the gulf but they are discounting chances for a diplomatic coup 
for the jordanian monarch and are reluctant to bet that lack of 
concrete action after the talks with bush will lead to gulf warfare 
in tokyo the dollar rose to a closing 14790 japanese yen from 
14715 yen at wednesdays close later in london it fell to 
14762 yen 
in london the british pound fell to 18985 from 19045 late 
wednesday 
