hewlettpackard co had a 5 percent 
drop in net earnings in the third quarter while earnings per share 
dipped from 79 cents to 73 cents the giant electronics company 
reported thursday 
in the quarter ending july 31 the company reported net earnings 
of 178 million compared to 187 million in the 1989 period 
revenues increased 8 percent in the quarter to 32 billion 
from 3 billion in the 1989 period 
were seeing a slowdown in a number of our businesses 
including test and measurement medical electronics pcs and 
workstations said john young the companys president and chief 
executive officer 
orders for the third quarter totaled 33 billion an increase 
of 9 percent from last years third quarter however the figure 
was down from 16 percent in the second quarter and 17 percent in 
the first 
a company statement also pointed out that the effective tax rate 
for the third quarter of fiscal 1990 was higher than for 1989s 
third quarter when an adjustment to the effective tax rate raised 
earnings by 5 cents a share 
the company said the earnings report reflects two months of 
results from apollo computer inc in the 1989 third quarter and 
three months during the same period of 1990 hp purchased apollo 
computer inc in may 1989 
for the first nine months of the fiscal year hp had net 
earnings of 537 million an 8 percent drop from 583 million in 
the 1989 period 
net revenues for the ninemonth period were 965 billion up 13 
percent from 852 billion in 1989 
