<TEXT>
grain and soybean futures prices closed narrowly 
mixed in lackluster trading thursday on the chicago board of trade 
as persian gulfrelated buying offset a persistently bearish tone 
in the markets 
a new round of warlike rhetoric from iraqi leader saddam hussein 
sent the stock market plunging and triggered sharp increases in 
crude oil and gold futures those events reignited inflation fears 
which lent support to the crop markets analysts said 
corn and soybean futures also were supported by talk of a 
possibility of frost in the northern corn belt monday night 
although analysts said the chances for frost in august were 
extremely slight 
selling pressure stemmed in part from a national weather service 
forecast predicting normal temperatures and rainfall in the midwest 
during the latter half of next week those conditions would benefit 
the corn and soybean crops in the region 
